        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the reference to the completion of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> (see n. 4, below).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Hooker, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1779.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Albert Günther</ref>, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3950.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Winwood Reade</ref>, and <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4642.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Robert Swinhoe</ref> came to Down on 28 January and left on 30 January 1871 (<ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1218.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Emma Darwin’s</ref> diary (DAR 242)). CD had corresponded with Reade while Reade was in West Africa (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vols. 16 and 17).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2366.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Henslow Hooker</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">According to his ‘Journal’ (Appendix II), CD finished correcting proofs of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> on 15 January 1871.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1222.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Francis Darwin</ref>.</note>
